1072. Flip Columns For Maximum Number of Equal Rows
Hint
You are given an m x n binary matrix matrix.

You can choose any number of columns in the matrix and flip every cell in that column 
(i.e., Change the value of the cell from 0 to 1 or vice versa).

Return the maximum number of rows that have all values equal after some number of flips.

Solution

class Solution:
    def maxEqualRowsAfterFlips(self, mat: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        pat_freq = Counter()
        
        for r in mat:
            pattern = tuple(r) if r[0] == 0 else tuple(bit ^ 1 for bit in r)
            pat_freq[pattern] += 1
            
        return max(pat_freq.values())


Input
matrix =
[[0,1],[1,1]]
Output
1
